.TH RUFUSARM64-PERSISTENCE 1 "20 July 2026" "RufusArm64 0.13.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
rufusarm64-persistence \- guarded persistent live-USB creator
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B rufusarm64-persistence
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B rufusarm64-persistence
opens the dedicated graphical workflow for supported Ubuntu casper and Debian
live-boot images. Compatibility analysis is read-only. Creation uses a fresh
GPT layout with a FAT32 live-media partition and an ext4 persistence partition.
.PP
The workflow is deliberately narrow. It refuses unrecognized boot layouts,
unsupported persistence contracts, unsafe targets, and images that cannot be
represented safely on FAT32. Creation remains identity-bound, requires exact
target confirmation and fresh administrator authentication, supports guarded
cancellation, and verifies the copied media and both filesystems.
.SH QUALIFICATION
Creation success does not prove physical boot or persistence across reboot.
Use the qualification commands documented in
/usr/share/doc/rufusarm64/persistence-qualification.md and retain the reports
for the exact image, USB, controller, firmware, and computer.
.PP
The optional package-owned ARM64 boot-time integrity loader is unsigned.
Secure Boot compatibility is not established.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR rufusarm64 (1),
.BR rufusarm64-cli (1)
